#Text=Gary Grainger
#Text=For the Australian footballer , see Gary Grainger ( footballer ) .
#Text=Gary Grainger ( born 20th century ) is an English rock , blues , jazz and pop songwriter and guitarist , most known for his work with Rod Stewart . [ 1 ]
#Text=Career
#Text=Gary Grainger 's professional career took off with the formation of Strider .
#Text=After two albums – Misunderstood and Exposed and two extensive tours with The Faces in 1974 , Grainger got his big break with Rod Stewart in 1976 .

#Text=The formation of the Rod Stewart group , including Jim Cregan , Phil Chen , Carmine Appice and Billy Peek , saw Grainger write key songs for the albums Foot Loose & Fancy Free , Blondes Have More Fun , and Foolish Behaviour .
#Text=Throughout 1986 and 1987 , Grainger worked with Roger Daltrey , with UK TV appearances on Number 73 and Saturday Live .
#Text=He played on Daltrey 's 1987 album , Ca n't Wait to See the Movie .
#Text=When Daltrey resumed activity with The Who and suspended solo work , Grainger formed a band with Jimmy Copley and Jaz Lochrie .
#Text=Grainger performed live and on TV appearances with Nick Lowe in support of Lowe 's Party of One album in 1990 .
#Text=He also appeared on Lowe 's 1994 album The Impossible Bird . [ 2 ]
#Text=In 1991 , Grainger formed The Humans with Jess Roden , Jim Capaldi , Bill Burke and Nick Graham .
#Text=The Humans recorded their first batch of songs at John Entwistle 's Hammerhead studios , with Bob Pridden as producer and engineer , with Steve Winwood on Hammond Organ .
#Text=Only " Railroad of Desire " was released from these recordings on 1995 's self-titled album .

column1: #Text=The band performed regularly throughout the UK and Europe until the late 1990s .
#Text=In the mid-nineties Grainger was recruited to produce and play guitar for the Brit Pop band The Face at the request of The Who 's long-time crew member Bob Pridden .
#Text=He played on the original recordings , during which time he recommended Zak Starkey for the sessions .
#Text=For live shows , Grainger opted out and The Face used Gary Nuttall , who went on to become long-time guitarist for Robbie Williams . [ 3 ]
#Text=In 1998 Grainger formed Blues Club with Alan Rogan .
#Text=Peter Hope-Evans of Medicine Head was on mouth organ and Kinks drummer Mick Avery joined .
#Text=They were initially recorded and produced by Pete Townshend with Jess Roden on vocals .
#Text=When Avery had other commitments , Chris Slade ( AC/DC ) joined on drums up until 2000 .
#Text=It was this line-up of Blues Club that appeared on BBC TV 's Casualty programme .
#Text=Blues Club continued for another decade , with Grainger 's son Chris replacing Avery and Slade on drums . [ 4 ]
#Text=2000 – present
#Text=In 2000 , Grainger received a call to work with Kenney Jones .
#Text=Initially collaborating for some charity gigs , the band proved popular and formed a more solid line-up featuring Boz Burrell on bass , Robert Hart on vocals .
#Text=Formula One racing champion Damon Hill joined the band on many of the early gigs . [ 5 ]
#Text=Their first recording was the charity single " It 's All About the Children " and was produced by the legendary Chris Kimsey .
#Text=The single also featured Paul Young on vocals .
#Text=Grainger played at the Ronnie Lane 2004 Tribute at the Royal Albert Hall onstage with Kenney Jones , Sam Brown , Ronnie Wood and Pete Townshend . [ 6 ]
#Text=In 2007 , Roger Daltrey played corporate shows in Canada .
#Text=Grainger was asked to join , playing Townshend 's parts along with The Who 's touring band of Zak Starkey , John " Rabbit " Bundrick , Simon Townsend and Phil Spalding played bass . [ 7 ]
#Text=From 2010 to 2012 , Grainger resumed working with Rod Stewart bandmate Jim Cregan in a project called " Apart From Rod " .

#Text=Touring the UK and Europe , Apart From Rod was a presentation of duo 's large catalogue of hits that they had written for Stewart , including Grainger 's songs " Hot Legs " , " Passion " , and " I Was Only Joking " . [ 8 ]
#Text=Musicians

#Text=Gary Grainger has worked with B.A. Robertson , Damon Hill , Rod Stewart , Danny Bowes , Jess Roden , Jim Capaldi , John Entwistle , Kenney Jones , Nick Lowe , Paul Carrack , Paul Young , Pete Townshend , Ringo Starr , Robert Hart , Roger Daltrey , Ronnie Wood , Sam Brown , and Strider . [ 9 ] [ 10 ] [ 2 ]
#Text=Personal life
#Text=Grainger was born in London and grew up in London 's Kilburn area .
#Text=He has one son , Chris Grainger , who is a drummer . [ 11 ]
